caption: Best food around!

I've gone to Daves probably close to 30 times at this point. It is by far the best Hot Chicken I've ever had. Everyone I've brought here has yet to be disappointed, and I've got all my coworkers hooked. Major bonus that it's halal!

Okay let's start off with the bad. I hate that they are only allowing you to order from Postmates! I honestly find that less safe. It would be okay if they added the option to order on Postmates for pickup, but they only allow delivery. I placed an order for two sandwiches and set the location for the same building that howlin rays is at. When I arrived, I waited outside to pick it up but there was no one there. I checked the Postmates app to see where the person was but it said they delivered the food? It's already not safe to have any close contact interaction with complete strangers handling your bag of food, but they didn't even make sure they were giving it to the right person is disappointing.
Wonderful and delicious coffee and omelette and French toast! Now I can see why locals frequent this place for a meal in a relaxed and leisurely setting!

Oh Moti, the man with the smile and the heart behind every mefuneket. Has been in business for over 30 years making every breakfast a warm welcoming one. When I was a kid he had the arcades and when I ran out of quarters he would pop some out of the register and give me another 4 with a wink on his face. His  wife and He treat my mom like a queen.  I’m 34 now and still getting mefuneket after mefuneket. May H’ give him the strength and health to carry on for many many more years. He has a lot of hungry people to feed.

caption: I finally stopped into this place a year after moving into the neighborhood. And I regret not going in earlier. The mefuneket is a delicious sandwich. It's simple, not overdone and the ingredients speak for themselves. Now I understand why this sandwich is so famous. When I ordered the sandwich, another customer said that I'd be coming back to this place. And they were right. I'll be back. Probably many times.
